  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ORPHANS AND VULNERABLE CHILDREN AND CHILD PROTECTION PROJECT</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at reducing vulnerability to HIV&amp;AIDS and improve status of PLWHA by improving access to education for orphans and vulnerable children (OVCs), which include support for early childhood development in Balaka and Phalombe districts. The project will strengthen the capacity of 100 caregivers in ECD, creating a conducive early ealry learning and stimulating environment by construction of 20 toilets, refurbishing 4 CBCCs and procure 200 CBCC kits. The project will also enhence advocancy and coordination skills on ECD and child protection issues at community level.</narrative>
  </description>
